<subSubSection id="19D76564990AFFB007B94898AB8A86C6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="517236EF990AFFB007B94898AB8A86C6" blockId="11.[151,1437,258,2028]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB007B94898A90486A2" bold="true" box="[199,326,1679,1704]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet is a concatenation of the Greek root 
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB004B24887AC4B86AD" box="[972,1033,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">aniso</emphasis>
(not equal) and 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB003C14887AD5286AD" box="[1215,1296,1680,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB003C14887AD5286AD" box="[1215,1296,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in reference to this species not being identical with 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB0053548A3AB8686C6" authority="Saigusa &amp; Yang, 2002" authorityName="Saigusa &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2002" box="[587,964,1715,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB0053548A3AAFC86C1" box="[587,702,1716,1739]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. serrata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="355C4B1E990AFFB005BB48A4AB8686C6" author="Saigusa" box="[709,964,1715,1740]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Saigusa, T. &amp; Yang, D. (2002) Empididae (Diptera) from Funiu mountains, Henan, China (I). Studia dipterologica, 9, 519 - 543." type="journal article" year="2002">
Saigusa &amp; Yang, 
<number id="E70524C8990AFFB004F648A3AB8686C6" box="[904,964,1716,1740]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="19D76564990AFFB707B948C0AB338117" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="517236EF990AFFB707B948C0AB338117" blockId="11.[151,1437,258,2028]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB007B948C0A97686FA" bold="true" box="[199,308,1751,1776]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks</emphasis>
. The two known examples of this species were taken during November from the vicinity of a waterfall at 
<quantity id="96359B0A990AFFB0066148EBA92A8719" box="[287,360,1788,1812]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.43" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="743.0">743 m</quantity>
in Loei Province, northeast 
<collectingCountry id="29DA767F990AFFB005D248ECAB52871E" box="[684,784,1787,1812]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="C9F62A6A990AFFB0045E48ECAB34871E" box="[800,886,1787,1812]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 81" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[296,1273,206,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[278,1289,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 81. Distribution of Hemerodromia spp. in Thailand at a resolution of 0.25 ° and symbols sized to 0.5 ° of latitude and longitude. 73, H. acutata Grootaert, Yang &amp; Saigusa; 74, H. alphalutea sp. nov.; 75, H. anisoserrata sp. nov.; 76, H. anomala sp. nov.; 77, H. attenuata sp. nov.; 78, H. betalutea sp. nov.; 79, H. conspecta sp. nov.; 80, H. deltalutea sp. nov.; 81, H. deminuta sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289959/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<number id="E70524C8990AFFB0042848ECAB34871E" box="[854,886,1787,1812]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="75.0">75</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB004F448ECAC888719" box="[906,1226,1787,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisoserrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB004F448ECAC888719" box="[906,1226,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hemerodromia anisoserrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB003AF48ECAD6E871E" bold="true" box="[1233,1324,1787,1812]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A5786990AFFB003AF48ECAD6E871E" box="[1233,1324,1787,1812]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is clearly closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB006194937AAA58732" authority="Saigusa &amp; Yang 2002" authorityName="Saigusa &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2002" box="[359,743,1823,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB006194937A99C873D" box="[359,478,1824,1847]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. serrata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="355C4B1E990AFFB006974908AAA58732" author="Saigusa" box="[489,743,1823,1848]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Saigusa, T. &amp; Yang, D. (2002) Empididae (Diptera) from Funiu mountains, Henan, China (I). Studia dipterologica, 9, 519 - 543." type="journal article" year="2002">
Saigusa &amp; Yang 
<number id="E70524C8990AFFB005D14937AAA58732" box="[687,743,1824,1848]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which was described from the Funui Mountains within the Qinling Range in central 
<collectingCountry id="29DA767F990AFFB006CF4954A9BA8756" box="[433,504,1859,1884]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">China</collectingCountry>
. The terminalia of 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB005B44953AB388751" box="[714,890,1860,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisoserrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB005B44953AB388751" box="[714,890,1860,1883]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. anisoserrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB004FF4954AB988756" bold="true" box="[897,986,1859,1884]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A5786990AFFB004FF4954AB988756" box="[897,986,1859,1884]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB003054953ACAF8751" box="[1147,1261,1860,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB003054953ACAF8751" box="[1147,1261,1860,1883]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="355C4B1E990AFFB002564954A954878A" author="Saigusa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Saigusa, T. &amp; Yang, D. (2002) Empididae (Diptera) from Funiu mountains, Henan, China (I). Studia dipterologica, 9, 519 - 543." type="journal article" year="2002">
Saigusa &amp; Yang 
<number id="E70524C8990AFFB007A5497FA954878A" box="[219,278,1896,1920]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 
<number id="E70524C8990AFFB006264970A9E2878A" box="[344,416,1895,1920]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="53.5" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="53.0">53–54</number>
) excepting that the apical process of the surstylus is less rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB003B9497FAD7F8775" box="[1223,1341,1896,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB003B9497FAD7F8775" box="[1223,1341,1896,1919]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the epandrium of 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB0064A499BA9A187A9" box="[308,483,1932,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisoserrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB0064A499BA9A187A9" box="[308,483,1932,1955]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. anisoserrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB00695499CAA0687AE" bold="true" box="[491,580,1931,1956]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A5786990AFFB00695499CAA0687AE" box="[491,580,1931,1956]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very different being apically truncate (distinctly pointed in 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB00384499BAD2F87A9" box="[1274,1389,1932,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB00384499BAD2F87A9" box="[1274,1389,1932,1955]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In addition the scutum of 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB006E349A7AA0C87CD" box="[413,590,1968,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisoserrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB006E349A7AA0C87CD" box="[413,590,1968,1991]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. anisoserrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB0052849B8AAF387C2" bold="true" box="[598,689,1967,1992]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A5786990AFFB0052849B8AAF387C2" box="[598,689,1967,1992]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is generally entirely yellow (three blackish longitudinal stripes in 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB007E949C3A94887E1" box="[151,266,2004,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB007E949C3A94887E1" box="[151,266,2004,2027]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990AFFB0063749C3A9BB87E1" box="[329,505,2004,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisoserrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB0063749C3A9BB87E1" box="[329,505,2004,2027]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">H. anisoserrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990AFFB0068149C4AA1A87E6" bold="true" box="[511,600,2003,2028]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A5786990AFFB0068149C4AA1A87E6" box="[511,600,2003,2028]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a yellowish mediotergite and lacks distinct scutellar setae. The present species is also closely similar to 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990DFFB705794E8EAAC680BA" box="[519,644,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990DFFB705794E8EAAC680BA" box="[519,644,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. ocellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990DFFB705F24E80AAA480BA" bold="true" box="[652,742,151,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A5786990DFFB705F24E80AAA480BA" box="[652,742,151,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
which has the narrow process emerging beyond the tip of the epandrium (lower lobe of surstylus?) linear rather than bent at 
<number id="E70524C8990DFFB704134EABABC980DE" box="[877,907,188,212]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="90.0">90</number>
° and bears two strong leaf-shaped specialised setae apically. 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C990DFFB706414EC8AA0980F2" box="[319,587,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990DFFB706414EC8AA0980F2" box="[319,587,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Hemerodromia ocellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD990DFFB7052A4EC8AAF280F2" bold="true" box="[596,688,223,248]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A5786990DFFB7052A4EC8AAF280F2" box="[596,688,223,248]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
